\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{example}
\meta{source}{[[axler-1996-linear]] Example 1.23}
\meta{source}{[[lankham-2016-linear]] Example 4.1.3}

\p{Let #{\FF} be a field. Then #{\FF^{\infty}} is the set of all sequences over #{\FF}. Then vector addition defined componentwise #{(u_{k})+(v_{k})=(u_{k}+v_{k})} and scalar multiplication defined componentwise #{a(u_{n})=(au_{n})} give us a vector space.}